tissueExpression.summary: Normal tissues generally displayed moderate nucleolar positivity. Strong staining was observed in a few tissues including exocrine pancreas, breast and neuronal cells. Glial cells were generally negative.
tissueExpression.validation: Mainly consistent with RNA expression data

image.description: Immunohistochemical staining of human breast shows strong nucleolar positivity in glandular cells.

tissueExpression.summary: Malignant cells generally showed moderate to strong nucleolar immunoreactivity. Most cases of malignant gliomas and renal cancers were weakly stained or negative.
